First Read: 15-Jan-26
HB254 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to vessels; to prohibit law enforcement
5 officers from stopping or boarding vessels for safety or
6 marine sanitation equipment inspections.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
8 Section 1. (a) A law enforcement officer may not stop
9 or board a vessel for the sole purpose of performing a safety
10 inspection or marine sanitation equipment inspection.
11 (b) For the purposes of this section, the term "vessel"
12 has the meaning as defined in Section 33-5-3, Code of Alabama
13 1975.
14 Section 2. This act shall become effective on June 1,
15 2026.
